issue.title: Make react-moment work with React 15.5+
issue.body:
Hi there ðŸ‘‹ 

First things first, thanks for all the work put into this awesome library!

In one of the projects I use it in, we just updated React to 15.5, which brought in some [deprecation warnings](https://facebook.github.io/react/blog/2017/04/07/react-v15.5.0.html#new-deprecation-warnings).

I figured I'd take it upon myself to try and help out with making this library work free of warning messages.

Also, I wasn't sure how you handled releases, so I left the version number untouched for the time being.

I hope you find this helpful/useful ðŸ˜„

comment.body: Thanks for the PR. I've merged the changes and I'm publishing them to npm now. :)
